class : 
class is a user defined data type used to define its properties.
syntax:
class classname
{
variable declaration;
variable declaration;
}
example:
class rectangle()
{
int length;
int width;
}

objec:
object is a member or an instance of class.
each object has its own identity ,behavior and state.
example :
Rectangle rect1(); //declaration
rect1=new Rectangle();
in this the variable rect1 is now an object at Rectangle class.

methods:
methods are declared inside the class .
syntax:
type methodname(parameters)
{
method body;
} 
example :
class Rectangle
{
int length, width;
int rectarea()  //defining  method
{
int area = length*width;
return (area);
}
}
public class rectarea
{
public static void main(String args[])
{
int area;
Rectangle rect = new Rectangle(); // creating objects 
rect.length = 15;
rect.width = 10;
area = rect.length*rect.width;
System.out.println("Area =" +area);
}
}
